AITrain Studio uses a harness-first development workflow.

At the beginning of every new task, automatically read:

- HARNESS.md
- docs/harness/current-status.md
- docs/harness/project-context.md
- docs/harness/implementation-checklist.md
- docs/harness/quality-gates.md

For UI work, also read:

- docs/harness/ui-guidelines.md

For large implementation work, also inspect:

- AITrainStudio_后续实施方案.md

Rules:

- Keep changes scoped.
- Preserve the Qt Widgets workbench architecture.
- Do not put long-running work in the GUI thread.
- Do not put training logic in MainWindow.
- Route long tasks through aitrain_worker.
- Use ProjectRepository for SQLite.
- Use plugin interfaces for model/dataset/export/inference behavior.
- Keep Qt 5.12+ compatibility unless explicitly changed.
- Use QStringLiteral for UI text.
- Avoid Chinese mojibake.
- Do not represent scaffold behavior as complete YOLO/OCR training.

Before finalizing code changes, run:

.\tools\harness-check.ps1
